---
layout: base.njk
pageType: home
title: proofstone — engineering roadmaps where every milestone is a proof
description: Engineering roadmaps where every milestone is a proof — a verifiable artifact, not a keyword. Built for working engineers.
---
<section class="hero">
  <h1 class="hero__title">{{ site.tagline }}</h1>
  <p class="hero__sub">{{ site.thesisSub }}</p>
  <p class="hero__series">
    {{ site.seriesLine }}
    <span class="hero__counts">{{ liveRoadmaps.length }} live · {{ reviewRoadmaps.length }} in review</span>
  </p>
</section>

<section class="roadmaps" aria-label="Roadmaps">
  {%- for r in liveRoadmaps %}
  <article class="card" data-accent="{{ r.accent }}">
    <a class="card__main" href="/{{ r.slug }}/">
      <h2 class="card__title">{{ r.title }}</h2>
      <p class="card__tagline">{{ r.tagline }}</p>
      <p class="card__meta">
        <span class="badge badge--count">{{ r.milestones }} milestones</span>
        <span class="badge badge--star">{{ r | roadmapStars }} ★ artifacts</span>
        <span class="card__go" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </p>
    </a>
    {%- if r.lab %}
    <p class="card__lab">
      <span class="card__lab-tag">lab</span>
      <a href="{{ r.lab.url }}" rel="noopener"><code>{{ r.lab.name }}</code></a> — {{ r.lab.note }}.
    </p>
    {%- endif %}
  </article>
  {%- endfor %}

  {%- for r in reviewRoadmaps %}
  <article class="card card--review" data-accent="{{ r.accent }}">
    <h2 class="card__title">{{ r.title }}</h2>
    <p class="card__tagline">{{ r.tagline }}</p>
    <p class="card__meta">
      <span class="badge badge--count">{{ r.milestones }} milestones</span>
      <span class="badge badge--star">{{ r | roadmapStars }} ★ artifacts</span>
      <span class="badge badge--review">In practitioner review — private until published</span>
    </p>
    {%- if r.labNote %}
    <p class="card__lab"><span class="card__lab-tag">lab</span> {{ r.labNote }}.</p>
    {%- endif %}
  </article>
  {%- endfor %}
</section>

<section class="sample" aria-label="What a milestone looks like">
  <h2 class="sample__title">What a milestone looks like</h2>
  <p class="sample__lead">Every node in every roadmap is one of these — taken here, unedited, from the AI Safety map.</p>
  <div class="prose sample__block">
    {%- for r in liveRoadmaps %}{% if r.sampleMilestone %}{{ r | milestoneSample(r.sampleMilestone) | safe }}{% endif %}{% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="how">
  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ol class="how__steps">
    <li><span class="how__num">1</span><span class="how__body"><strong>You're done when …</strong> Each node states one finishing condition, in advance.</span></li>
    <li><span class="how__num">2</span><span class="how__body"><strong>An artifact.</strong> Meeting it leaves something outside your head — a merged eval, a green test suite, a fabricated board.</span></li>
    <li><span class="how__num">3</span><span class="how__body"><strong>Proof.</strong> The artifact is the evidence. Nothing here is finished by reading about it.</span></li>
  </ol>
</section>

{#- Related work sits here for the same reason it sits near the end of every
    roadmap README: it is a footnote to the argument, not part of it. The reader
    has just been told what a milestone is, which is what makes "this one has no
    milestones" mean something. #}
<section class="companions" aria-labelledby="companions-heading">
  <h2 class="companions__heading" id="companions-heading">Companion projects</h2>
  <p class="companions__lead">
    Standalone repositories alongside the series. Not roadmaps themselves — no milestones,
    no finishing conditions — but the maps link into them from the inside.
  </p>

  {#- A block-paragraph, not a grid: there is one companion, and a one-cell
      catalogue reads as a row that failed to load. A second one appends another
      .companion here and nothing else changes.
      The owner is spelled out in the link text on purpose — this repository
      lives in a personal account, not in the proofstone org, and the page must
      not imply otherwise. #}
  <div class="companion">
    <h3 class="companion__name">
      <span class="companion__tag">index</span>
      <a href="https://github.com/TheSeydiCharyyev/build-your-own-agent" rel="noopener"><code>TheSeydiCharyyev/build-your-own-agent</code></a>
    </h3>
    <p class="companion__note">
      An index, not a map. For each of the ten components of the agent stack it points at the
      best from-scratch tutorials that exist elsewhere; for the three where none did — MCP
      server and client, coding agent, token accounting — it ships a runnable reference
      implementation of its own, zero dependencies and no API key. The AI Safety map links
      into it twice and states the relation there: that roadmap proves an agent is safe,
      this repository is the half where you make one work.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="thesis">
  <h2>Why proof, not keywords</h2>
  <p>{{ site.thesis }}</p>
  <p class="thesis__contribute">
    The roadmap repositories are the source of truth — this site is the render layer.
    Contribute by opening a pull request on a roadmap's repo; the site rebuilds itself.
    <a href="{{ site.org }}" rel="noopener">github.com/proofstone →</a>
  </p>
</section>
